The paper deals with filter banks, which are commonly used in signal processing and information theory. The paper also mentions multidimensional or cyclic filter banks, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of frames and perfect reconstruction conditions suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also provides a unified way of studying filter banks for signals in $\ell^2(\mathbb{Z}^d\times \mathbb{Z}_s)$ or $\ell^2(\mathbb{Z}_r \times \mathbb{Z}_s)$ spaces, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Overall, cs.IT and cs.SP are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM, with cs.SI being the least likely.
